ng%20Russia's%20military%20potential%2C%20not%20Ukraine's%20draft%20age%2C%26quot%3B%20continued%20the%20post.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20goal%20should%20be%20to%20preserve%20as%20many%20lives%20as%20possible%2C%20not%20to%20preserve%20weapons%20in%20storages.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20post%20was%20in%20response%20to%20US%20State%20Department%20Spokesperson%20Matthew%20Miller's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.c-span.org%2Fvideo%2F%3F540474-1%2Fstate-department-spokesperson-holds-briefing-fall-syrian-regime%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecomment%20on%20Monday%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20US%20was%20ready%20to%20train%20and%20arm%20new%20soldiers%20if%20Ukraine%20changed%20its%20conscription%20policy.%20The%20current%20minimum%20conscription%20age%20is%2025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20we%20have%20made%20clear%20is%20that%20if%20they%20produce%20additional%20forces%20to%20join%20the%20fight%2C%20we%20and%20our%20allies%20will%20be%20ready%20to%20equip%20those%20forces%20and%20train%20those%20forces%20to%20enter%20battle%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Miller%20in%20a%20press%20briefing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZelenskyy%20previously%20resisted%20the%20idea%20in%20November%20when%20an%20anonymous%20US%20administration%20official%20told%20reporters%20that%20reducing%20the%20draft%20age%20would%20help%20Ukraine%20keep%20up%20with%20Russia's%20military.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20simple%20truth%20is%20that%20Ukraine%20is%20not%20currently%20mobilizing%20or%20training%20enough%20soldiers%20to%20replace%20their%20battlefield%20losses%20while%20keeping%20pace%20with%20Russia's%20growing%20military%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20senior%20official%20had%20said%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2F328141b2-fc6e-43a1-aa6b-262358b9ac0e%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EThe%20Financial%20Times.%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20speech%20to%20the%20parliament%2C%20Zelenskyy%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BLet%20there%20be%20no%20speculation%20%E2%80%94%20our%20state%20is%20not%20preparing%20to%20lower%20the%20mobilization%20age.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZelenskyy%20has%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwest-always-gives-ukraine-weapons-year-after-needs-them-zelenskyy-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Erepeatedly%20expressed%20frustration%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20delays%20in%20military%20aid%20from%20Ukraine's%20Western%20allies%2C%20on%20whom%20it%20is%20dependent%20for%20advanced%20weapons%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fatacms-storm-shadow-missiles-rain-down-on-russia-first-time-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EPatriot%20and%20Storm%20Shadow%20missiles.%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20manpower%20shortages%20on%20the%20battlefield%20remain%20a%20key%20problem%20for%20the%20Ukrainians.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWar%20analyst%20Michael%20Kofman%20told%20BI%20earlier%20this%20year%20that%20Ukraine's%20%26quot%3Bmanning%20situation%20is%20the%20kind%20of%20thing%20that's%20probably%20going%20to%20get%20worse%20before%20it%20gets%20better.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20year%2C%20a%20Ukrainian%20service%20member%20told%20The%20Washington%20Post%20that%20the%20companies%20in%20his%20battalion%20were%20staffed%20at%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-still-has-major-problem-that-us-aid-fix-russia-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E35%25%20of%20normal%20levels%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-zelenskky-us-pressure-draft-18-year-old-manpower-shortage-2024-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1733829785000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6758206052dd0818d1a