-love-broke-up-still-live-here-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESpain%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20lucky%20that%20my%20parents%20supported%20most%20of%20my%20way%20through%20university%2C%20so%20I%20wasn't%20coming%20to%20Spain%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20student%20loans%20or%20debt.%20I%20also%20worked%20at%20Starbucks%20during%20college%20and%20had%20about%20%2412%2C000%20in%20savings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20I%20didn't%20know%20anyone%20and%20wasn't%20exactly%20sure%20what%20I%20was%20getting%20myself%20into.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221070%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Kenzie%20Wallace%20(middle)%20at%20the%20Madrid%20palace%20with%20friends.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67530dae8fbb2783ed3032f5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWallace%20(middle)%20in%20Madrid%20with%20friends%20she%20made%20during%20her%20first%20year%20in%20Spain.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Kenzie%20Wallace%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20moved%20to%20the%20country%20on%20an%20English%20teaching%20visa%20through%20Spain's%20language%20assistant%20program.%20The%20program%20contracts%20native%20English%20speakers%20to%20work%20in%20public%20schools%2C%20teaching%20English%20immersion%20classes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20applied%20before%20arriving%20in%20the%20country%2C%20secured%20a%20part-time%20teaching%20job%20that%20earned%20me%20about%20%241%2C000%20a%20month%2C%20and%20was%20assigned%20to%20a%20school.%20For%20my%20first%20two%20weeks%20in%20Madrid%2C%20I%20stayed%20with%20a%20host%20family%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20those%20two%20weeks%20were%20up%2C%20I%20had%20to%20figure%20out%20housing%20on%20my%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221462ec61-3dab-4bc0-8530-d507d8994e01%5C%22%3EI%20had%20to%20figure%20out%20life%20in%20Spain%20on%20my%20own%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEventually%2C%20I%20found%20an%20apartment%20on%20real-estate%20website%20Idealista%20for%