veloped%20a%20first-of-its-kind%20graphics%20program%20in%20which%20computer%20users%20could%20string%20together%20a%20series%20of%20slides.%20Originally%20called%20Presenter%2C%20it%20was%20released%20in%20April%201987%2C%20as%20PowerPoint.%20Microsoft%20immediately%20saw%20its%20world-changing%20potential%2C%20buying%20Forethought%20just%20four%20months%20later%20for%20%2414%20million.%20For%20one%20thousandth%20of%20the%20nearly%20%2414%20billion%20the%20company%20has%20invested%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-mind-of-sam-altman-openai-ceo-worldview-interviews-writing-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpenAI%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Microsoft%20acquired%20a%20program%20that%20remains%20arguably%20more%20consequential%20to%20how%20businesses%20operate.%20By%201993%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-ai-artificial-intelligence-bet-doubts-marc-benioff-satya-nadella-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMicrosoft%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20raking%20in%20%24100%20million%20from%20PowerPoint%20sales%20a%20year%3B%20by%202003%2C%20%241%20billion.%20Microsoft%20estimated%20that%2030%20million%20PowerPoint%20presentations%20were%20being%20made%20every%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDecks%20have%20no%20shortage%20of%20zealots%2C%20including%20my%20former%20boss.%20When%20I%20worked%20at%20BarkBox%2C%20Nick%20Cogan%2C%20a%20vice%20president%20of%20creative%2C%20always%20had%20us%20making%20decks%20%E2%80%94%20not%20just%20for%20big%20retail%20pitches%20but%20for%20every%20little%20task.%20Product%20planning%2C%20style%20guide%2C%20whatever%20it%20was%2C%20we'd%20make%20a%20deck.%20I%20maybe%20want%20him%20to%20apologize%20for%20all%20the%20deck%20wrangling%2C%20but%20he%20laughs%20and%20doesn't%20give%20an%20inch%20defending%20them%2C%20which%2C%20as%20a%20former%20animator%2C%20he%20loves%20for%20their%20storytelling%20capabilities.%20%26quot%3B'Look%20at%20this%2C%20not%20us'%20can%20be%20essential%20when%20presenting%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20He%20describes%20the%20perfect%20presentation%20as%20both%20a%20%26quot%3Buseful%20crutch%26quot%3B%20and%20a%20%26quot%3Blittle%20kids'%20storybook%2C%26quot%3B%20where%20he%20can%20walk%20the%20great%20and%20mighty%20decision-makers%20through%20storytime%20instead%20of%20business%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChristina%20Farr%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmaven-ipo-chrissy-farr-womens-health-startup-prediction-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehealthtech%20director%20and%20investor%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20wrote%20a%20book%20about%20storytelling%20in%20business%2C%20agrees%2C%20arguing%20that%20the%20deck%20actually%20draws%20its%20power%20%3Cem%3Efrom%3C%2Fem%3E%20its%20ubiquity.%20Because%20people%20are%20used%20to%20both%20writing%20and%20receiving%20decks%2C%20%26quot%3Bpeople%20know%20what%20the%20story%20should%20sound%20like%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20expected%20rhythms%20and%20beats%20of%20a%20PowerPoint%20presentation%20%26quot%3Bare%20already%20baked%20in.%26quot%3B%20But%20it's%20not%20just%20an%20emotional%20expectation%2C%20she%20says%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20also%20a%20formal%20one%3A%20%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20raising%20money%2C%20in%202024%2C%20you%20have%20to%20have%20a%20deck.%20Everybody%20expects%20you%20to%20do%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrue%2C%20but%20there's%20also%20been%20no%20shortage%20of%20deck%20denigrators.%20In%202003%2C%20the%20media%20theorist%20Edward%20Tufte%20published%20%26quot%3BThe%20Cognitive%20Style%20of%20PowerPoint%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20remains%20one%20of%20the%20most%20deliciously%20damning%20indictments%20of%20a%20software%20program%20ever%20written.%20Over%20several%20thousand%20words%2C%20Tufte%20flamb%C3%A9s%20PowerPoint%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Bslideware%26quot%3B%20in%20general%2C%20for%20%26quot%3Bmaking%20us%20stupid%2C%20degrading%20the%20quality%20and%20credibility%20of%20our%20communication%2C%20turning%20us%20into%20bores%2C%20wasting%20our%20colleagues'%20time.%26quot%3B%20Though%20PowerPoint%20was%20developed%20and%20even%20celebrated%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bcure%20for%20the%20presentation%20jitters%2C%26quot%3B%20Tufte%20maligns%20it%20as%20overly%20oriented%20toward%20the%20presenter%2C%20leaving%20little%20room%20for%20the%20listener%20to%20chime%20in%20or%20even%20actively%20listen.%20Tufte%20even%20goes%20so%20far%20as%20to%20blame%20PowerPoint's%20%26quot%3Bpoverty%20of%20content%26quot%3B%20and%20its%20%26quot%3Bforeshortening%20of%20evidence%20and%20thought%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20Space%20Shuttle%20Columbia%20disaster.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20jeremiad%20had%20many%20admirers%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbillionaire-bunker-miami-bezos-tom-brady-ivanka-trump-security-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJeff%20Bezos%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Inspired%20by%20Tufte%2C%20the%20Amazon%20CEO%20in%20June%202004%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjeff-bezos-email-against-powerpoint-presentations-2015-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebanned%20PowerPoint%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20executive%20meetings.%20The%20book%20%26quot%3BWorking%20Backwards%3A%20Insights%2C%20Stories%2C%20and%20Secrets%20from%20Inside%20Amazon%26quot%3B%20describes%20Bezos%20as%20finding%20slide%20decks%20%26quot%3Bfrustrating%2C%20inefficient%2C%20error-prone%2C%26quot%3B%20with%20a%20stiff%20format%20that%20%26quot%3Bmade%20it%20difficult%20to%20evaluate%20actual%20progress.%26quot%3B%20In%20its%20place%20the%20company%20developed%20what's%20become%20known%20as%20the%20Amazon%20Six-Pager%3A%20a%20detailed%20memo%20outlining%20%E2%80%94%20in%20narrative%20prose%2C%20not%20bullet%20points%20%E2%80%94%20the%20conversations%20and%20business%20problems%20that%20have%20surfaced%20the%20need%20for%20a%20meeting.%20In%20a%20deck%2C%20information%20takes%20a%20back%20seat%20to%20form%20and%20format%3B%20the%20memo%2C%20in%20contrast%2C%20forces%20the%20presenter%20to%20embody%20a%20Joan%20Didion%20axiom%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20know%20what%20I%20think%20until%20I%20write%20it%20down.%26quot%3B%20Attendees%20read%20the%20six-pager%20%3Cem%3Ebefore%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%20meeting%2C%20so%20everyone%20can%20enter%20the%20meeting%20informed%20and%20be%20held%20accountable%20for%20the%20decisions%20made%20out%20of%20the%20discussion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224528%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Steve%20Ballmer%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6757964cdc8b666017f23677%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223014%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIn%202011%2C%20Steve%20Ballmer%20maligned%20decks%20while%20he%20was%20CEO%20of%20PowerPoint%20maker%20Microsoft.%20Before%20meetings%20he%20told%20employees%2C%20%26quot%3BPlease%20don't%20present%20the%20deck.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3ESteven%20Ferdman%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20hate%20the%20way%20people%20use%20slide%20presentations%20instead%20of%20thinking%2C%26quot%3B%20Steve%20Jobs%20once%20opined%2C%20adding%20that%20%26quot%3Bpeople%20who%20know%20what%20they're%20talking%20about%20don't%20need%20PowerPoint.%26quot%3B%20Even%20Steve%20Ballmer%2C%20who%20sits%20atop%20literal%20millions%20and%20owns%20the%20Los%20Angeles%20Clippers%20in%20part%20because%20of%20PowerPoint%20money%2C%20maligned%20decks%20%3Cem%3Ewhile%3C%2Fem%3E%20he%20was%20CEO%20of%20Microsoft.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20it's%20efficient%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%202011%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BMost%20meetings%20nowadays%2C%20you%20send%20me%20the%20materials%20and%20I%20read%20them%20in%20advance.%20And%20I%20can%20come%20in%20and%20say%3A%20'I've%20got%20the%20following%20four%20questions.%20Please%20don't%20present%20the%20deck.'%26quot%3B%20Over%20the%20years%2C%20many%20members%20of%20the%20US%20military%20have%20cast%20aspersions%20toward%20what%20they%20call%20%26quot%3Bdeath%20by%20PowerPoint.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20incentive%20structures%20for%20a%20slide%20deck%20are%20all%20bad%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Aviv%20Gilboa%2C%20the%20president%20of%20Skylight%2C%20a%20consumer%20tech%20company%20known%20for%20its%20digital%20picture%20frames%20and%20calendars.%20To%20Gilboa%2C%20who%20worked%20at%20Amazon%20for%20four%20years%2C%20decks%20aren't%20just%20boring%2C%20they're%20antithetical%20to%20many%20ways%20we%20think%20and%20work.%20The%20format%20of%20a%20single%20slide%20is%20inherently%20low-information%3A%20When%20you're%20pitching%2C%20you're%20persuading%2C%20and%20so%20you%20can%20fit%20only%20one%20idea%20per%20slide%2C%20often%20forcing%20you%20to%20leave%20some%20good%20ideas%20behind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGilboa%20says%20decks%20also%20help%20presenters%20feel%20good%20without%20forcing%20them%20to%20engage%20with%20their%20decisions.%20Decks%20help%20reinforce%20this%20perception%20of%20assurance%2C%20what%20Gilboa%20calls%20%26quot%3Bthe%20smoke%20and%20mirrors%20of%20how%20we%20got%20to%20this%20choice.%26quot%3B%20As%20I%20sat%20at%20BarkBox%20making%20decks%20every%20which%20way%20for%20every%20little%20business%20problem%2C%20I%20felt%20like%20a%20purveyor%20of%20both%20smoke%20and%20mirrors%2C%20no%20matter%20what%20my%20boss%20said%20about%20storytelling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20our%20workplace%20problems%20have%20evident%20solutions%20made%20possible%20by%20software%20%E2%80%94%20for%20example%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-docs-publicly-available-ai-training-settings-private-shared-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle%20Docs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20miracle%20program%20that%20replaced%20back-and-forth%20documents%20and%20version%20control%20with%20fluid%2C%20collaborative%20workflow.%20But%20like%20many%20in%20the%20PowerPoint%20mines%2C%20I'm%20not%20sure%20what%20alternative%20could%20possibly%20replace%20slides%20at%20scale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EZeck%20was%20born%20in%202022%20out%20of%20its%20cofounders'%20rage%20at%20decks%2C%20especially%20in%20board%20meetings.%20%26quot%3BAt%20our%20prior%20companies%2C%20the%20shortest%20deck%20we%20ever%20sent%20was%20134%20pages%2C%26quot%3B%20Zeck's%20cofounder%20Robert%20Wolfe%20tells%20me%2C%20adding%20that%20%26quot%3Bthere%20was%20nothing%20more%20stressful%26quot%3B%20about%20preparing%20for%20those%20meetings.%20He%20says%20that%20at%20CrowdRise%2C%20the%20company%20he%20ran%20with%20his%20brother%20Jeffrey%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fglass-onion-edward-norton-dressed-tom-cruise-magnolia-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEdward%20Norton%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20they'd%20stop%20all%20other%20work%20for%20100%20hours%20before%20every%20board%20meeting%20in%20order%20to%20write%20and%20build%20the%20quarterly%20decks%20they%20hated%20enough%20to%20found%20Zeck.%20In%20a%20nod%20to%20Norton%2C%20Wolfe%20integrated%20a%20%26quot%3BFight%20Club%26quot%3B%20reference%20into%20the%20origin%20story%20on%20Zeck's%20website%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20meeting%20I%20just%20sat%20through%20was%20like%20the%20scene%20in%20Fight%20Club%20where%20you%20punch%20yourself%20in%20the%20face%20over%20and%20over.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227956%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Edward%20Norton%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F675794e891c1cc343d478fd6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225304%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThree-time%20Academy%20Award-nominated%20actor%20Edward%20Norton%20cofounded%20Zeck%20in%202022%20to%20disrupt%20the%20ubiquity%20of%20slide%20decks.%3Cp%3EPATRICK%20T.%20FALLON%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20Wolfe%2C%20the%20deck%20model%20%26quot%3Bliterally%20creates%20antagonism%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20everyone%20becomes%20an%20editor%20with%20a%20red%20pen%2C%20the%20deck%20presenting%20endless%20entry%20points%20for%20criticism.%20In%20the%20military%20or%20an%20everyday%20office%2C%20grunts%20and%20junior%20designers%20hate%20working%20on%20PowerPoints%2C%20tweaking%20pixels%20and%20making%20rounds%20of%20edits%20that%20drive%20everyone%20crazy%2C%20because%20in%20PowerPoint%20you're%20often%20not%20working%20on%20the%20idea%2C%20but%20only%20on%20the%20presentation%20of%20the%20idea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZeck%20proposes%20that%20the%20solution%20to%20the%20deck%20is%20a%20collaborative%20website.%20A%20Zeck%20site%20feels%20a%20bit%20like%20a%20Notion%20site%20but%20with%20tweaks%20that%20work%20well%20for%20the%20boardroom%20%E2%80%94%20it%20gives%20everyone%20edit%20access%2C%20is%20encrypted%2C%20can%20be%20personalized%2C%20and%20offers%20links%20so%20that%20your%20chief%20financial%20officer%20or%20finance%20team%20can%20access%20full%20reports%20and%20charts%20and%20important%20information.%20It%20is%20a%20revelation%20to%20not%20have%20that%20information%20simplified%20in%20a%20slide%20in%20a%20meeting%20where%20everyone%20has%20to%20sit%20through%20everything.%20And%20in%20Zeck's%20pitch%20I%20find%20a%20great%20clarity%20equaled%20so%20far%20only%20by%20Tufte%20himself%3A%20When%20we%20remove%20the%20awful%20slide%20deck%2C%20once%20again%20%26quot%3Bthe%20meeting%20can%20be%20a%20meeting.%26quot%3B%20So%20far%2C%20Zeck%20counts%20among%20its%20clients%20Hard%20Rock%20Hotel%20%26amp%3B%20Casino%2C%20furniture%20maker%20Floyd%2C%20and%20the%20rocket%20startup%20Phantom%20Space%20Corporation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Zeck%20is%20unlikely%20to%20supplant%20PowerPoint%20any%20time%20soon%2C%20Wolfe%20thinks%20people%20are%20finally%20rebelling%20against%20the%20idea%20%26quot%3Bthat%20you%20only%20have%20Office%20and%20all%20the%20tools%20that%20go%20with%20it%2C%20or%20a%20Google%20Drive%20and%20all%20the%20tools%20that%20go%20with%20it.%26quot%3B%20He%20makes%20a%20brazen%20prediction%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20would%20be%20shocked%20if%20in%2018%20months%20or%20five%20years%20people%20are%20still%20using%20flat%20slides%20for%20meetings%20that%20should%20be%20collaborative.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20aren't%20yet%20letting%20go%20of%20decks%20in%20business%2C%20but%20we've%20let%20them%20hop%20the%20fence%20into%20our%20wider%20culture%2C%20both%20celebrating%20and%20undermining%20their%20repressive%20formality%20and%20ubiquity.%20The%20post-irony%20generations%20are%20throwing%20%26quot%3BPowerPoint%20parties%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20some%20singles%2C%20sick%20of%20dating%20apps%2C%20are%20using%20PowerPoint%20to%20make%20their%20cases%20as%20mates.%20A%202021%20episode%20of%20the%20Bravo%20reality%20show%20%26quot%3BSummer%20House%26quot%3B%20featured%20a%20subplot%20built%20around%20a%20romantic%20gesture%20delivered%20via%20PowerPoint.%20For%20some%2C%20slides%20may%20be%20a%20love%20language.%20There%20are%20even%20famous%20decks%20now%2C%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstarboard-transforming-darden-restaurants-2014-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethis%20300-pager%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20which%20a%20hedge-fund%20excoriated%20Olive%20Garden's%20business%20practices%2C%20or%2C%20my%20favorite%2C%20Jennifer%20Egan's%20PowerPoint%20chapter%20from%20her%202010%20Pulitzer%20Prize-winning%20novel%2C%20%26quot%3BA%20Visit%20from%20the%20Goon%20Squad.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEgan%20tells%20me%20she%20got%20a%20crash%20course%20in%20the%20program%20from%20her%20business-world%20sister%2C%20who%20%26quot%3Bthinks%20in%20PowerPoint.%26quot%3B%20The%20formal%20experiment%20of%20a%20PowerPoint%20chapter%20was%20exciting%2C%20though%20the%20%26quot%3Bcold%2C%20corporate%20vibe%26quot%3B%20was%20perhaps%20incompatible%20with%20real%2C%20genuine%20emotion%20and%20the%20stuff%20contained%20in%20great%20novels.%20She%20suggests%20this%20tension%20gives%20the%20finished%20chapter%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3BGreat%20Rock%20and%20Roll%20Pauses%2C%26quot%3B%20the%2012-year-old%20protagonist%20Alison%20Blake's%20account%20of%20her%20autistic%20brother's%20favorite%20pauses%20in%20classic%20rock%20songs%20interspersed%20with%20descriptions%20of%20their%20mom%20and%20dad%20coming%20and%20going%2C%20fighting%20and%20reflecting%20%E2%80%94%20its%20power.%20The%20chapter%20delivers%20earnest%20emotion%20without%20being%20schlocky%2C%20and%20is%20brave%20and%20hilarious%20without%20being%20corny.%20Egan%20says%20she%20isn't%20typically%20this%20type%20of%20writer%2C%20but%20the%20PowerPoint%20format%20gave%20her%20the%20ability%20to%20tell%20%26quot%3Bthis%20very%20sweet%20story%20in%20a%20cold%20holder.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20the%20PowerPoint%20parties%20and%20Egan%20have%20it%20right%20and%20we%20should%20let%20PowerPoint%20do%20what%20it%20does%20best%3A%20tell%20stories.%20For%20Egan%2C%20a%20deck%20arguably%20won%20a%20Pulitzer.%20For%20NASA%2C%20a%20deck%20arguably%20killed%20astronauts.%20In%20the%20big%20middle%20between%20those%20outcomes%2C%20we're%20still%20deciding%20whether%20a%20story%20is%20always%20what's%20necessary%20%E2%80%94%20and%20what%20to%20do%20about%20decks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fmatt-alston%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EMatt%20Alston%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E's%20writing%20has%20appeared%20in%20Wired%2C%20Rolling%20Stone%2C%20Playboy%2C%20and%20Believer.%20He%20trained%20as%20a%20civil%20engineer%2C%20and%20now%20works%20as%20a%20copywriter%20in%20tech.%20He%20lives%20in%20Maine%20with%20his%20wife%20and%20daughter.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-jeff-bezos-edward-norton-killing-powerpoint-good-luck-2024-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1733821321000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67575a0fdc8b666017f21e8a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-jeff-bezos-ed