r%20blue%20skies%2C%20the%20smooth%20roads%20on%20which%20our%20children%20were%20cycling%20around%2C%20shrieking%20with%20joy%2C%20the%20acres%20of%20rolling%20greens%20of%20public%20parks%20around%20us%20and%20the%20white%20buildings%20at%20the%20far%20end%E2%80%94our%20local%20Palo%20Alto%20library%2C%20recreation%20centre%2C%20public%20pool%2C%20children's%20museum%20and%20zoo.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20shut%20my%20eyes%2C%20nodding%20mutinously.%20%E2%80%9CI'm%20sure.%20Facilities%20aren't%20everything.%20I%20want%20my%20children%20to%20know%20who%20they%20are%2C%20their%20rich%20culture%2C%20heritage%2C%20their%20ethnic%20identity%2C%20their%20grandparents%2C%20cousins%20and%20extended%20family.%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%9CSo%20do%20I.%20Family%20visits%20once%20a%20year%E2%80%94and%20my%20kids%20are%20learning%20bharatnatyam%2C%20tabla%20and%20flute%20right%20here.%20And%20they%20go%20to%20after-school%20Hindi%20classes%2C%E2%80%9D%20another%20friend%20exclaimed.%20She%20had%20managed%20to%20get%20Hindi%20included%20in%20the%20seven%20foreign%20languages%20taught%20after%20school.%20%E2%80%9CPlus%20they%20can%20cycle%20to%20most%20of%20these%20places%20by%20themselves%20by%20the%20time%20they%20are%20teens.%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%9CIt's%20not%20the%20same%2C%20it's%20not%20immersive%2C%20experiential%E2%80%A6.organic.%20They%20are%20forced%20to%20toggle%20between%20two%20worlds%2C%E2%80%9D%20I%20insisted%2C%20not%20even%20bringing%20up%20the%20difference%20between%20planned%20annual%20visits%20and%20meeting%20nani%2C%20dadi%2C%20maasi%2C%20bua%20and%20cousins%20at%20will.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAnd%20you're%20willing%20to%20give%20up%20all%20civic%20amenities%20for%20that%3F%20Have%20you%20forgotten%20the%20dust%2C%20grime%2C%20pollution%2C%20and%20disease%20-%20not%20to%20mention%20the%20corruption%2C%20beginning%20from%20the%20petty%20to%20the%20sublime%3F%E2%80%9D%20said%20another%20college%20friend%20sarcastically.%20She%20had%20recently%20got%20her%20citizenship%20after%20nearly%20a%20decade%20of%20living%20here.%20%E2%80%9CLook%2C%20you're%20just%20months%20away%20from%20converting%20your%20Green%20Card%20to%20full%20citizenship.%20Why%20don't%20you%20wait%20another%20year%2C%20become%20a%20citizen%20and%20then%20return%3F%E2%80%9D%20advised%20another%20reasonably.%20%E2%80%9CThat's%20what%20we%20did%E2%80%94and%20now%20we%20come%20and%20go%20as%20we%20please.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHome%20And%20Denial%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20between%20our%20idealism%20and%20our%20practical%20calculations%2C%20intertwined%20with%20our%20desire%20to%20raise%20our%20children%20in%20our%20homeland%2C%20we%20not%20just%20left%2C%20but%20also%20gave%20up%20our%20green%20card%2C%20which%2C%20as%20an%20Australian%20friend%20reminded%20me%20severely%2C%20%E2%80%9Cpeople%20risk%20their%20lives%20on%20boats%20in%20open%20seas'%20to%20get%E2%80%9D.%20Delhi%20welcomed%20us%20with%20monsoon%20rains%20and%20mangos.%20We%20were%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFast%20forward%20a%20couple%20of%20years%2C%20in%20the%20winter%20of%202012%2C%20I%20found%20myself%20in%20denial%20about%20something%20other%20parents%2C%20mostly%20expats%2C%20were%20calling%20toxic%20air.%20Delhi's%20air%20pollution%20was%20sickening%20and%20killing%20us.%20It%20was%20much%20worse%20than%20Beijing's%20pollution%2C%20but%20less%20known.%20And%20that%20winter%20haze%20I%20used%20to%20call%20a%20fog%20was%20actually%20a%20poisonous%20smog%20that%20enveloped%20my%20city%20of%20birth%20and%20choice.%20It%20took%20me%20another%20two%20years%2C%20many%20conversations%20with%20air%20pollution%20experts%2C%20reading%20research%20papers%2C%20and%20searching%20the%20web%20to%20be%20thoroughly%20convinced%20that%20what%20we%20were%20breathing%20was%20dangerous%20to%20our%20health%2C%20that%20every%20breath%20compromised%20our%20health%20and%20that%20every%20newborn%20was%20a%20smoker.%20We%20had%20to%20do%20something%20to%20save%20our%20children%20and%20our%20parents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EFive%20Things%20We%20Don't%20Understand%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20us%20banded%20together%20to%20bring%20awareness%20and%20advocate%20for%20clean%20air%2C%20making%20detailed%20presentations%20at%20schools%2C%20hospitals%20and%20residential%20areas%2C%20talking%20to%20children%2C%20parents%2C%20teachers%20and%20doctors%2C%20petitioning%20the%20courts%20and%20making%20individual%20changes%20from%20composting%20all%20kitchen%20waste%20to%20switching%20to%20public%20transport%20and%20EVs.%20In%20this%2012-year%20journey%E2%80%9410%20years%20of%20which%20I%20spent%20fighting%20for%20clean%20air%E2%80%94I've%20learnt%20more%20than%20I%20wanted%20to%20know%20about%20disease%2C%20disability%20and%20death%20due%20to%20air%20pollution.%20Ironically%2C%20my%20own%20mother%20passed%20away%20from%20lung%20cancer%20which%20her%20doctors%20said%20was%20triggered%20by%20air%20pollution.%20I've%20had%20to%20send%20my%20kids%20away%20sooner%20than%20I%20had%20planned%2C%20and%2C%20in%20the%20end%2C%20I%20myself%20became%20a%20pollution%20refugee.%20Here%20are%20the%20top%20five%20things%20that%20many%20still%20don't%20realise%20about%20this%20killer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20there%20are%20no%20safe%20levels%20of%20air%20pollution.%20Experts%20speak%20in%20one%20voice%20when%20they%20say%20this%2C%20whether%20it%20is%20the%20World%20Health%20Organisation%2C%20the%20National%20Institutes%20of%20Health%2C%20the%20American%20Journal%20of%20Respiratory%20and%20Critical%20Care%20Medicine%20or%20others.%20Episodic%20high%20pollution%20levels%2C%20like%20what%20happens%20during%20peak%20stubble%20burning%20or%20Diwali%2C%20may%20dramatically%20increase%20visits%20to%20hospital%20emergency%20rooms%2C%20but%20even%20relatively%20lower%20pollution%20levels%20cause%20disease%2C%20disability%20and%20death.%20Almost%201.7%20million%20people%20die%20from%20air%20pollution%20each%20year%2C%20which%20is%20more%20than%20three%20times%20the%20deaths%20Covid-19%20caused%20in%20one%20year%2C%20a%20disease%20the%20Indian%20government%20took%20seriously%20in%20its%20public%20messaging%E2%80%94something%20it%20has%20never%20done%20with%20equal%20intensity%20for%20pollution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecond%20and%20equally%20important%2C%20air%20pollution%20is%20not%20a%20seasonal%20problem.%20It%20is%20an%20invisible%2C%20year-round%20problem%20in%20all%20of%20India%20that%20usually%20becomes%20more%20visible%20in%20the%20winter.%20On%20average%2C%20the%20country's%20pollution%20load%20is%20usually%2010%20times%20higher%20than%20the%20WHO%20guidelines%20all%20year%20through.%20It%20is%20just%20insanely%E2%80%94almost%2050%20times%E2%80%94higher%20in%20the%20winter%20months%20in%20north%20India%2C%20which%20leads%20to%20international%20headlines%20and%20increased%20attention.%20However%2C%20that%20doesn't%20alter%20the%20fact%20that%20year-round%20pollution%20levels%20are%20also%20high.%20Sadly%2C%20they%20have%20been%20normalised%20by%20over%20a%20billion%20people%20torn%20between%20helplessness%2C%20resignation%20and%20apathy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EDon't%20Blame%20North%20India%20Alone%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThird%2C%20over%2090%25%20of%20India%20breathes%20dirty%20air%2C%20not%20just%20northern%20India%20or%20Delhi%2C%20though%20these%20regions%20are%20the%20most%20highly%20polluted.%20The%20Indo-Gangetic%20plain%20is%20home%20to%2040%25%20of%20India's%20population%2C%20which%20means%20more%20than%20500%20million%20people%20are%20sickened%20by%20just%20breathing.%20But%20Mumbai%20has%20shown%20us%20in%20three%20consecutive%20years%20that%20it%20can%20beat%20Delhi's%20AQI%20levels%2C%20last%20year%20even%20a%20month%20before%20Diwali.%20As%20for%20southern%20India%2C%20although%20its%20geography%20(high%20altitude)%20and%20weather%20(rain%20and%20wind)%20ensures%20most%20of%20its%20particulate%20matter%20is%20washed%20or%20blown%20away%2C%20Bengaluru%20had%20the%20dubious%20distinction%20of%20topping%20the%20State%20of%20Global%20Air's%20list%20of%20polluted%20cities%20for%20nitrous%20oxides%20in%20September%202023%2C%20followed%20by%20neighbouring%20Hyderabad.%20NOx%20exacerbates%20respiratory%20diseases%2C%20and%20a%20recent%20AIIMS%20study%20found%20it%20can%20lead%20to%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20number%20of%20emergency%20room%20visits%20by%2053%25.%20Another%20coastal%20city%2C%20Chennai%2C%20has%20had%20its%20moments%2C%20with%20AQI%20levels%20crossing%20Delhi%20levels.%20And%20if%20you%20thought%20that%20only%20urban%20India%20was%20suffering%2C%20not%20only%20does%20research%20show%20that%20pollution%20is%20increasing%20faster%20in%20southern%20and%20eastern%20India%2C%20it%20is%20also%20growing%20in%20rural%20areas%2C%20where%20indoor%20air%20pollution%20(caused%20by%20burning%20biomass%20for%20cooking%20and%20heating)%20already%20contributes%20nearly%2030%25%20of%20outdoor%20air%20pollution.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFourth%2C%20air%20pollution%20doesn't%20harm%20just%20the%20human%20respiratory%20system%20but%20damages%20every%20organ%20in%20the%20human%20body%2C%20especially%20the%20heart.%20Peer-reviewed%20journal%20Neurology's%20September%20issue%20published%20research%20that%20showed%20a%20strong%20and%20significant%20correlation%20between%20air%20pollutants%20and%20death%20from%20strokes.%20In%20fact%2C%20Bengaluru%20has%20the%20youngest%20population%20of%20heart%20patients.%20The%20city's%20Jayadeva%20Institute%20of%20Cardiovascular%20Science%20and%20Research%20treated%202%2C200%20heart%20attacks%20of%20patients%20under%2040%20in%20two%20years%2C%20the%20youngest%20being%2016%20years%20old.%20These%20were%20mostly%20software%20professionals%20and%20auto%2Fcab%20drivers%20who%20spent%20longer%20than%20an%20hour%20in%20traffic.%20But%20is%20sixteen%20any%20age%20to%20have%20a%20heart%20attack%20triggered%20by%20just%20the%20involuntary%20act%20of%20breathing%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThere's%20No%20Going%20Back%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENone%20of%20this%20harm%20is%20short-term.%20It%20is%20long-term%20and%20irreversible%2C%20which%20means%20that%20you%20can%20only%20arrest%20it%20once%20you%20start%20breathing%20clean%20air%20(like%20when%20you%20stop%20smoking%20cigarettes).%20Those%20microscopic%20particles%20of%20PM2.5%20that%20you're%20inhaling%20right%20now%3F%20They%20will%20remain%20in%20your%20body%20until%20you%20die.%20The%20University%20of%20Chicago%20has%20created%20an%20Air%20Quality%20of%20Life%20Index%20tool%20that%20calculates%20how%20much%20longer%20people%20of%20a%20certain%20region%20would%20live%20on%20average%20if%20that%20region%20met%20WHO%20guideline%20limits.%20A%20Delhi%20resident%20would%20live%20nearly%2012%20years%20longer%2C%20and%20a%20north%20India%20resident%20nearly%20seven%20years%20if%20the%20air%20they%20breathed%20met%20WHO%20guidelines.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELastly%2C%20let%20me%20not%20even%20get%20started%20about%20how%20air%20pollution%20is%20a%20social%20inequity%2C%20this%20column%20just%20doesn't%20have%20enough%20words%20for%20that.%20But%20when%20you%20are%20working%20from%20home%20with%20your%20air%20purifier%20on%20a%20high%20pollution%20day%2C%20spare%20a%20thought%20for%20the%20waste-picker%20or%20construction%20worker%20who%20won't%20get%20her%20daily%20wage%20if%20she%20decides%20to%20protect%20her%20health%20and%20stay%20home%2C%20or%20the%20traffic%20policeman%20who%20stands%20among%20vehicular%20fumes%20at%20intersections%20directing%20traffic%2C%20or%20the%20autorickshaw%20driver%20who%20won't%20earn%20if%20he%20doesn't%20drive%20one%20day.%20These%20are%20also%20people%20who%20have%20less%20access%20to%20healthcare%20and%20are%20often%20malnourished.%20By%20now%2C%20we%20know%20air%20pollution%20is%20the%20greatest%20threat%20to%20human%20health%20globally%2C%20whose%20impact%20on%20life%20expectancy%20is%20comparable%20to%20that%20of%20smoking%2C%20more%20than%20three%20times%20that%20of%20alcohol%20use%20and%20unsafe%20water%2C%20six%20times%20that%20of%20HIV%2FAIDS%2C%20and%2089%20times%20that%20of%20conflict%20and%20terrorism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia's%20air%20has%20been%20getting%20filthier%20over%20the%20years.%20Politicians%20bring%20up%20economic%20growth%20as%20the%20bogey%20when%20urged%20to%20act%20strongly%20and%20decisively%20on%20pollution.%20But%20there%20is%20a%20difference%20between%20growth%20and%20development%20-%20with%20the%20latter%20including%20a%20better%20quality%20of%20life%20through%20a%20focus%20on%20basic%20needs%20for%20all%2C%20healthcare%2C%20education%20and%20well-being.%20That%20is%20the%20kind%20of%20sustainable%20growth%20I'd%20like%20to%20see%20in%20my%20country%2C%20a%20place%20I%20chose%20to%20return%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Jyoti%20Pande%20Lavakare%20is%20the%20author%20of%20the%20grief%20memoir%20'Breathing%20Here%20is%20Injurious%20to%20Your%20Health'%C2%A0and%20co-founder%2C%20Care%20for%20Air.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1733816940000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2Fajv24la8_air_625x300_10_December_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fyou-must-outrage-over-filthy-air-more-than-once-a-year-7214249%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Delhi%20welcomed%20us%20with%20monsoon%20rains%20and%20mangos.%20We%20were%20home.%20Fast%20forward%20a%20couple%20of%20years%2C%20in%20the%20winter%20of%202012%2C%20I%20found%20myself%20in%20denial%20about%20something%20other%20parents%2C%20mostly%20expats%2C%20were%20calling%20toxic%20air.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fyou-must-outrage-over-filthy-air-more-than-once-a-year-7214249%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Indian%20Students%20See%2038%25%20Drop%20In%20US%20Visas%20Issued%20From%20Jan%20To%20September%202024%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIndian%20students%20are%20witnessing%20a%20massive%20drop%20in%20study%20visas%20issued%20to%20them.%20The%20latest%20data%20from%20the%20US%20State%20Department%20shows%20there%20was%20a%2038%20per%20cent%20decline%20in%20F-1%20student%20visas%20issued%20to%20Indian%20nationals%20in%20the%20first%20nine%20months%20of%202024%20compared%20to%20the%20same%20period%20in%20the%20previous%20year.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EData%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22No%20Follow%2C%20No%20Index%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftravel.state.gov%2Fcontent%2Ftravel%2Fen%2Flegal%2Fvisa-law0%2Fvisa-statistics%2Fnonimmigrant-visa-statistics%2Fmonthly-nonimmigrant-visa-issuances.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBureau%20of%20Consular%20Affairs%3C%2Fa%3E'%20monthly%20reports%20show%20Indian%20students%20were%20granted%2064%2C008%20F-1%20visas%20between%20January%20and%20September%20this%20year%2C%20a%20steep%20fall%20from%201%2C03%2C495%20visas%20issued%20during%20the%20same%20period%20in%202023.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20least%20number%20of%20visas%20issued%20to%20Indian%20students%20since%20the%20pandemic-affected%202020%2C%20when%20just%206%2C646%20requests%20were%20considered%20during%20the%20same%20timeframe.%20In%20a%20post-pandemic%20rebound%2C%20a%20total%20of%2093%2C181%20Indian%20students%20were%20given%20F-1%20visas%20between%20January%202022%20and%20September%202022%2C%20while%20in%202021%2C%20the%20number%20stood%20at%2065%2C235.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20decline%20is%20not%20unique%20to%20Indian%20students%2C%20as%20Chinese%20students%2C%20the%20second%20largest%20international%20cohort%20in%20the%20US%2C%20also%20witnessed%20an%208%20per%20cent%20decline%20in%20the%20issuance%20of%20F-1%20visas%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20official%20data%2C%20a%20total%20of%2073%2C781%20F-1%20visas%20were%20issued%20to%20Chinese%20students%20in%20the%20first%20nine%20months%20of%202024%2C%20down%20from%2080%2C603%20issued%20during%20the%20same%20time%20frame%20in%202023.%20The%20number%20was%2C%20however%2C%20still%20higher%20than%20the%2052%2C034%20F-1%20visas%20issued%20to%20Chinese%20students%20in%202022.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EAbout%20F1%20Visa%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20F-1%20visa%20is%20a%20non-immigrant%20visa%20which%20permits%20international%20students%20from%20across%20the%20world%20to%20study%20full-time%20in%20the%20United%20States.%20It%20is%20the%20most%20common%20visa%20status%20for%20students%20from%20other%20countries%20in%20the%20US.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20in%202024%2C%20Indians%20surpassed%20Chinese%20non-migrants%20to%20become%20the%20largest%20cohort%20of%20overseas%20students%20in%20the%20United%20States.%20As%20per%20the%20Open%20Doors%202024%20report%2C%203%2C31%2C000%20Indian%20students%20were%20studying%20in%20US%20institutions%20during%20the%202023-24%20academic%20year%2C%20compared%20to%202%2C68%2C923%20the%20previous%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20count%20of%20Chinese%20students%20declined%20in%20the%20US.%20The%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22No%20Follow%2C%20No%20Index%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fopendoorsdata.org%2Ffact_sheets%2Fstudent-mobility%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpen%20Doors%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%20report%20said%20there%20were%202%2C77%2C398%20Chinese%20students%20in%20the%20US%20in%202023-24%2C%20nearly%2012%2C000%20less%20than%202%2C89%2C526%20in%202022-23.%20China%20also%20witnessed%20an%208%20per%20cent%20decline%20in%20the%20issuance%20of%20F-1%20visas%20in%202024.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1733816880000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2017-03%2Fus-universities-us-students-650-400_650x400_71490607358.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Findian-students-see-38-drop-in-us-f-1-visas-issued-in-2024s-1st-nine-months-7214410%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20latest%20data%20from%20the%20US%20State%20Department%20shows%20there%20was%20a%2038%20per%20cent%20decline%20in%20F-1%20student%20visas%20issued%20to%20Indian%20nationals%20in%20the%20first%20nine%20months%20of%202024%20compared%20to%20the%20same%20period%20in%20the%20previous%20year.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Findian-students-see-38-drop-in-us-f-1-visas-issued-in-2024s-1st-nine-months-7214410%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Rahul%20Gandhi's%20Role%20In%20Question%3F%20More%20INDIA%20Leaders%20Back%20Mamata%20Banerjee%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIn%20another%20sign%20that%20the%20Congress%20is%20getting%20cornered%20within%20the%20INDIA%20bloc%2C%20RJD%20founder%20and%20veteran%20politician%20Lalu%20Prasad%20Yadav%20today%20said%20Trinamool%20Congress%20chief%20Mamata%20Banerjee%20should%20lead%20the%20Opposition%20alliance%20and%20that%20the%20Congress's%20objection%20to%20this%20%26quot%3Bmeans%20nothing%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCongress's%20objection%20means%20nothing.%20We%20will%20support%20Mamata...%20Mamata%20Banerjee%20should%20be%20given%20the%20leadership%20(of%20the%20INDIA%20Bloc)%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20veteran%20leader%20said%20when%20asked%20about%20Ms%20Banerjee's%20remarks%20on%20leading%20the%20INDIA%20bloc.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20month%2C%20in%20a%20veiled%20swipe%20at%20the%20Congress%2C%20the%20West%20Bengal%20Chief%20Minister%20had%20said%20%26quot%3Beveryone%20needs%20to%20be%20taken%20along%26quot%3B%20as%20the%20Opposition%20bloc%20moves%20against%20the%20BJP-ruled%20central%20government.%C2%A0Asked%20why%20she%20was%20not%20taking%20charge%2C%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BIf%20given%20the%20opportunity%2C%20I%20would%20ensure%20its%20smooth%20functioning.%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20go%20outside%20Bengal%2C%20but%20I%20can%20run%20it%20from%20here.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20remarks%20over%20INDIA%20bloc's%20leadership%20play%20out%20against%20the%20backdrop%20of%20the%20ongoing%20Winter%20Session%20of%20Parliament.%20Differences%20have%20cropped%20up%20on%20the%20strategy%20the%20Opposition%20must%20follow%20to%20corner%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20in%20the%20House.%20While%20the%20Congress%2C%20led%20by%20Leader%20of%20the%20Opposition%20Rahul%20Gandhi%2C%20demanded%20a%20discussion%20on%20the%20Adani%20indictment%20issue%2C%20leading%20to%20frequent%20adjournments%2C%20the%20Trinamool%20insisted%20that%20it%20wants%20the%20House%20to%20function%20so%20that%20it%20can%20raise%20key%20issues%20such%20as%20price%20rise%2C%20unemployment%20and%20the%20Manipur%20unrest.%20MPs%20of%20the%20Trinamool%20and%20Samajwadi%20Party%20--%20the%20biggest%20opposition%20forces%20after%20the%20Congress%20--%20were%20conspicuously%20missing%20from%20an%20Opposition%20protest%20over%20the%20Adani%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Gandhi%20has%20been%20pushing%20hard%20on%20the%20Adani%20issue%20after%20a%20US%20Department%20of%20Justice%20indictment%20against%20the%20directors%20of%20Adani%20Green.%20The%20Adani%20Group%20has%20maintained%20that%20Gautam%20Adani%2C%20his%20nephew%20Sagar%20Adani%2C%20and%20senior%20executive%20Vneet%20Jaain%20are%20clear%20of%20bribery%20charges.%20Gautam%20Adani%20has%20said%20this%20is%20not%20a%20challenge%20the%20group%20has%20faced%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3Bevery%20attack%20makes%20us%20stronger%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20had%20consolidated%20its%20position%20as%20the%20main%20Opposition%20party%20after%20scoring%2099%20seats%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20doubling%20its%202019%20tally.%20But%20the%20setbacks%20in%20the%20Haryana%20and%20Maharashtra%20polls%20have%20given%20way%20to%20rumblings%20within%20the%20Opposition%20camp.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20Shiv%20Sena%20(UBT)%20leader%20Sanjay%20Raut%20had%20said%20Ms%20Banerjee%20should%20be%20a%20major%20partner%20of%20the%20INDIA%20alliance.%20%26quot%3BWe%20know%20this%20opinion%20of%20Mamata%20ji.%20We%20also%20want%20her%20to%20be%20a%20major%20partner%20of%20the%20INDIA%20alliance.%20Whether%20it%20is%20Mamata%20Banerjee%2C%20Arvind%20Kejriwal%20or%20Shiv%20Sena%2C%20we%20are%20all%20together.%20We%20will%20soon%20go%20to%20talk%20to%20Mamata%20Banerjee%20in%20Kolkata%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20had%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20party%20colleague%20Priyanka%20Chaturvedi%20had%20said%20the%20Trinamool%20chief%20had%20repeatedly%20fended%20off%20the%20BJP%20offensive%20in%20Bengal.%20%26quot%3BBecause%20she%20has%20shown%20a%20successful%20model%20in%20West%20Bengal%20where%20she%20has%20kept%20the%20BJP%20away%20from%20power%20and%20implemented%20good%20welfare%20schemes...her%20election%20experience%2C%20and%20fighting%20spirit%2C%20accordingly%20she%20has%20shared%20her%20interest.%20Whenever%20the%20INDIA%20bloc%20meeting%20takes%20place%2C%20our%20senior%20leaders%20will%20together%20take%20a%20decision%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20had%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVeteran%20politician%20and%20NCP%20founder%20Sharad%20Pawar%2C%20too%2C%20has%20voiced%20support.%20%26quot%3BYes%2C%20certainly%20(she%20is%20capable%20of%20leading%20the%20alliance).%20She%20is%20a%20prominent%20leader%20of%20this%20nation...%20she%20has%20that%20capability.%20The%20elected%20leaders%20she%20sent%20to%20Parliament%20are%20responsible%2C%20dutiful%2C%20and%20well-aware%20people.%20Therefore%2C%20she%20has%20the%20right%20to%20say%20so%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Pawar%20had%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20INDIA%20bloc%20was%20formed%20last%20year%20when%20the%20Opposition%20parties%20decided%20to%20work%20out%20their%20ideological%20differences%20and%20fight%20the%20formidable%20BJP%20together.%20The%20grand%20alliance%20strategy%20worked%20well%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20and%20the%20ruling%20BJP%20was%20res